The following scripts allow cleaning a Docker host, and stopping and deleting containers and images.
Stop all containers:
#!/bin/bash CONTAINERS=$(docker ps -a | tail -n+2 | cut -d&#34; &#34; -f1) if [ &#34;$CONTAINERS&#34; == &#34;&#34; ]; then exit fi docker stop $CONTAINERS Stop and delete all containers:
